《'''星星狐'''》是一部由[[厦门青鸟动画|厦门青鸟动画]]製作的[[中国动画|中国动画]]，在[[中国中央电视台|中国中央电视台]]播映。

在2013年[[意大利波隆那童書展|意大利波隆那童書展]]，Trajectory Inc.從厦门青鸟取得《星星狐》的世界性發行权。<ref>Reid, Calvin. "[http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/childrens/childrens-book-news/article/56513-trajectory-inks-e-book-deals-with-chinese-publishers-at-bologna-book-fair.html Trajectory Inks e-Book Deals with Chinese Publishers at Bologna Book Fair]" ([http://www.webcitation.org/6Ozsu4D0q Archive]). 《[[出版者周刊|出版者周刊]]》. March 25, 2013. Retrieved on April 21, 2014. "Trajectory also inked a deal with the Xiamen Bluebird Cartoon Company of China to distribute more than 50 e-books based on Xingxing Fox, a popular Chinese animated TV series about a brave quick-witted fox that lives in a magic forest.[...]while Xingxing Fox is one of the most popular kids’ characters on Chinese TV and winner of numerous broadcasting awards."</ref>

Trajectory Inc.計劃出版50冊《星星狐》电子书。<ref name=ChinaDailyebook>Berg, Caroline. "[http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/epaper/2013-03/26/content_16346081.htm E-book deals signed for Chinese fairy tales]" ([http://www.webcitation.org/6OzsdXjTH Archive]). 《[[中国日报|中国日报]]》. March 26, 2013. Retrieved on April 21, 2014. "In its partnership with Xiamen Bluebird Cartoon Co, Trajectory will help develop more than 50 e-books based on Xingxing Fox, a popular Chinese animated TV series about a brave, quick-witted fox that lives in a magical forest. The Xingxing Fox series will initially be available in English only. Bryant said Trajectory has the capability to translate stories into any language the publisher wants its works distributed."</ref>

